  "text": "Specimens for electron microscopy were fixed for 1 h at 25°C in 1 % glutaraldehyde (Polysciences, Inc ., Warrington, Pa .) buffered with PBS, pH 7 .4. Postfixation was done with 170 osmium tetroxide (Polysciences) in PBS at 25°C for 1 h. In some experiments, a third fixation was done with 670 uranyl acetate in distilled H2O [CITATION_1] for I h at 25°C. Samples were dehydrated in a series of ethanols graded from 70 to 100c/c , after which they were transferred to 100°,0 propylene oxide before embedding in Epon 812 .",
